         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">202 Pitt Street ¶ Sydney 27th Decr /93 ¶ My Dear Baron, ¶  ¶ I have much pleasure in forwarding you a specimen of a Grevillea discovered by my son ¶  on the Cole River about 75 miles south of Sydney. ...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">93.12.27</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">From Patrick Shepherd</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">RB MSS M1, Library, Royal Botanic Gardens Melbourne.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">MS found with a specimen of <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Grevillea asplenifolia</seg> (MEL 14280), with M's standard label dated 1893 and a note attached to a seed-packet, dated Dec. 1893, both giving the name 'Grevillea asplenifolia var Shepherdi' and the collector Shepherd. The standard herbarium label also gives the locality as 'near Jarvis-Bay, NSW' (overwriting 'Jervois').</p>
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>MS annotation by M: 'Rec &amp; answ 29/12/93 F.v.M'. Letter not found.</p>
               </note>202 Pitt Street</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">Sydney 27th Decr /93</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">My Dear Baron,</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I have much pleasure in forwarding you a specimen of a Grevillea discovered by my son<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Lindesay Shepherd (1858-1933); see notes to P. Shepherd to M, 19 January 1894.</p>
               </note> on the Cole River about 75 miles south of Sydney. The flower is almost identical with G. longifolia but the leaves are much longer and are not serrated as are those of longifolia I will be glad if you will kindly let me know if you have met with this variety before and if so what is its name.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I have not had the pleasure of seeing you for a very long time, but it is probable I will pay a visit to Melbourne in the course of two or three months in which case I will do myself the great pleasure of paying you a visit. Wishing you the best Compliments of the Season</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">I remain</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Dear Baron von Mueller,</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Yours very sincerely</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>P. L. C. Shepherd<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">MS annotation by M underneath the signature: 'P. L. C. Shepherd'. See also P. Shepherd to M, 19 January 1894.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Baron von Mueller K.C.M.G.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Melbourne</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Grevillea%20longifolia">Grevillea longifolia</name>
            </p>
